fire on the outskirts of kalispell mont were allowed to return 
saturday after crews managed to get a line around the 120acre 
blaze no homes were lost although several were threatened 
we only have one road closed and thats to try to find out 
where it the fire started said flathead county deputy sheriff 
phil caperton authorities believed the blaze which broke out 
friday was mancaused 
hundreds of firefighters battled about a halfdozen other fires 
in western montana two fires were being allowed to run their 
course because they are in wilderness areas including the canyon 
creek fire in the scapegoat wilderness north of ovando authorities 
closed about 75000 acres of the 250000acre wilderness on 
saturday due to the blaze 
marcia hogan a forest spokeswoman said the blaze grew 
substantially saturday but that no estimate on its size was 
available because smoke obscured much of the area earlier the 
fire was reported to have consumed 2000 acres 
a brush fire about eight miles north of canon city colo grew 
to 1700 acres saturday afternoon as about 330 firefighters and 
aircraft battled the blaze in steep terrain on cooper mountain 
bureau of land management spokesman ken smith blamed the growth 
of the fire on winds 
the wind has changed directions about three times today and 
now its fairly calm again smith said the blaze which broke 
out thursday is named the dinosaur fire because it is near a 
fossil site 
before the dinosaur fire fires had burned about 21000 acres 
across colorado since last weekend the other fires were all 
contained by thursday 
in southern california a fire sparked by fireworks was 
contained saturday after it burned about 420 acres of the san 
bernardino national forest near yucaipa said us forest service 
spokeswoman melody fountain 
and in northern california firefighters finally contained two 
fires in calaveras county after the blazes charred about 10800 
acres dick craig a spokesman for the california department of 
forestry said full control of the blazes was expected by monday 
night 
damage from the fires totaled 11 million including timber and 
property losses and fire suppression efforts said sharon torrence 
a spokeswoman for the cdf in rail road flat 150 miles east of san 
francisco and a few miles west of the fires 
six homes nine other buildings and eight vehicles were lost 
since the arsonsuspected blazes broke out tuesday 
also saturday firefighters battled a 200acre brush fire near 
flaming gorge dam on the utahcolorado border and several small 
fires near salt lake city authorities said 
